by Sauros » Wed Jun 29, 2022 8:59 pm

Damnit, I jumped the gun and then missed it. Guess I'll put this here anyway:

Monkey 1, after witnessing the complete annihilation of the rest of its species, wondered if the extinction of the monkeys would actually be beneficial to the cosmos. It means that new life can develop in the niches previously occupied by other monkeys; and it also means that should the human race go extinct, there will be less of a chance (however slim, still less) for a "new humanity" to re-evolve through convergent evolution (simply because there will be less primates). Regardless, Monkey 1 knew the end was inevitable, and so it did what any sane being would do: the monkey injected its own conciousness into a holoprogram, so that while the monkeys end up extinct, its own existence shalt not be cut short.

Centuries later, the U.S.S. Defiant finds a capsule floating in space, and transfers it to the nearest Starfleet research ship for scientific analysis. It turns out to be a primitive form of a holoprogram created before they came into existence, which should be impossible. Regardless, it is activated, and the program turns out to be the stored conciousness of a monkey; the conciousness takes on the form of what it used to be, and the crew affectionately dub it "Bobo".
